{{Quote|They call us Balawai, don't they?|Roly Melusar|<ref name="SWG">''[[Imperial Commando: 501st]]''</ref>}}
Living on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Haruun Kal/Legends|Haruun Kal]], the '''Balawai''', or '''Downfolk''', were a social group of indeterminate [[Species/Legends|species]] who fought with the [[Korun/Legends|Korunnai]], the natives of the planet, during the [[Summertime War]]. 96% of the Balawai were [[Human/Legends|humans]], although the term also encompassed the various alien settlers as well, among whom were [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]], [[Kubaz/Legends|Kubaz]], [[Yuzzem]], [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]], [[t'landa Til]], [[Kitonak/Legends|Kitonak]], [[Pho Ph'eahian]], [[Yarkora/Legends|Yarkora]], and [[Togorian/Legends|Togorians]].

The Balawai were offworld settlers to the Korunnai, arriving mainly to collect the expensive [[Spice/Legends|spices]] that were native to Haruun Kal. They completely controlled the world's civil government, funding it mainly through the [[thyssel bark]] trade. They used [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]] instead of hand-crafted weapons.

During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the some Balawai sided with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], mainly due to the fact that at the start of the war there was a [[Judicial Department/Legends|Judicial Department]] investigation into whether the [[Representative Council|Balawai government]] had been infringing upon the rights of the Korunnai. After the [[Battle of Haruun Kal/Legends|Battle of Haruun Kal]], the Summertime Wars were ended, and the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] negotiated a peace between the Korunnai and the Balawai.

The name ''Balawai'' was a nomenclature meaning ''downfolk'', coined by the Korunnai and used only by the Korunnai. The immigrants on Haruun Kal thought of themselves simply as their own races. To call one of the Balawai such to their face would be a grave insult.

